                   "message":  "EGUIHOST-MENU-EXTRACTION: move menu construction to a submodule, retire exemption\n\nPure structural move (behaviour-identical), the dedicated follow-up #304\u0027s EXEC\nflagged. Extracts the cohesive menu-construction block out of\ncrates/editor-egui-host/src/lib.rs into a new crates/editor-egui-host/src/menu.rs\nsubmodule so the host crate root drops back under the §1.3 Rule-3 1000-line cap\nand the split-cap exemption MENU-SHORTCUT-DISPLAY (#304) re-added is RETIRED.\nMirrors EGUIHOST-TEST-EXTRACTION (#301), which split the inline tests out as its\nown dispatch.\n\n- New menu.rs (pub(crate)): the four extension-point consts, build_main_menu_entries,\n  play_item_enabled, and menu_item — VERBATIM bodies + a module doc + its own\n  rge_editor_ui::menus import.\n- lib.rs: `mod menu;` + `use menu::{build_main_menu_entries, menu_item,\n  play_item_enabled};` (render + new() call sites unchanged); menus import reduced\n  to just Command; the one `[MenuRegistry]` field-doc link fixed to a full path;\n  the `// SPLIT-EXEMPTION:` annotation REMOVED. lib.rs 1062 -\u003e 836 lines.\n- menu_tests.rs: use/doc-link repoint to crate::menu::; module-doc cap note updated\n  (drops the now-false \"carries a split-cap exemption\" line).\n\nBehaviour-identical: registration order, accelerator values, and every test\nassertion are byte-unchanged; only the symbols\u0027 module path moved. No editor-ui /\neditor-shell / Cargo.toml change; no new crate edge; 0 split-exemption markers\ncrate-wide.\n\nGate: VERIFY OK 7/7 + 10/10 arch lints (split-exemption PASS, lib.rs \u003c 1000);\ncargo check/test/fmt clean (24 lib + integration tests pass).\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e",
